statements: SELECT * FROM patient_outcomes WHERE outcome = 'Improved';
SELECT patient_id, treatment_protocol FROM patient_outcomes WHERE treatment_protocol = 'Medication A';
SELECT outcome FROM patient_outcomes WHERE patient_id = 100;
SELECT patient_id, outcome FROM patient_outcomes WHERE patient_id > 50;
SELECT * FROM patient_outcomes WHERE treatment_protocol LIKE '%surgical%';
SELECT * FROM patient_outcomes WHERE outcome = 'Success';
SELECT patient_id, outcome FROM patient_outcomes WHERE patient_id > 100 ORDER BY outcome DESC;
SELECT treatment_protocol FROM patient_outcomes WHERE outcome = 'Failure' OR outcome = 'Incomplete' ORDER BY patient_id ASC;
SELECT * FROM patient_outcomes WHERE treatment_protocol LIKE '%A%' AND outcome != 'Incomplete';
SELECT AVG(patient_id) AS avg_patient_id, COUNT(*) AS total_outcomes FROM patient_outcomes GROUP BY treatment_protocol HAVING COUNT(*) > 1 ORDER BY avg_patient_id DESC;

SELECT * FROM patients JOIN outcomes ON patients.patient_id = outcomes.patient_id JOIN treatments ON outcomes.treatment_id = treatments.treatment_id WHERE patients.gender = 'Male' ORDER BY treatments.success_rate DESC
SELECT treatments.treatment_name, AVG(cost) AS avg_cost FROM treatments JOIN outcomes ON treatments.treatment_id = outcomes.treatment_id GROUP BY treatments.treatment_name HAVING AVG(cost) > 5000
